{"id":"hep-ph/9701273","submitter":"Sergei Kovalenko","authors":"M. Hirsch, H.V. Klapdor-Kleingrothaus and S.G. Kovalenko","title":"B-L-violation in Softly Broken Supersymmetry and Neutrinoless Double\n  Beta Decay","comments":"8 pages, Latex, 1 Postscript figure","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We prove a low-energy theorem valid for any model of weak scale softly broken\nsupersymmetry. It claims that the neutrino Majorana mass, the B-L violating\nmass of the sneutrino and the neutrinoless double beta decay amplitude are\nintimately related to each other such that if one of them is non-zero the other\ntwo are also non-zero and, vice versa, if one of them vanishes the other two\nvanish as well. The theorem is a consequence of the underlying supersymmetry\nand independent of the mechanisms of neutrinoless double beta decay and\n(s-)neutrino mass generation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Jan 1997 14:40:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
